# Zitadel IdP for `<project-name>` (2.0.0 candidate)

This directory is the **2.0.0 identity delta** for the `full-stack-monorepo`
flagship. It introduces **Zitadel** as the project's first Identity Provider
(IdP), authored as an **additive** sibling alongside the frozen flat 1.0.0
template tree — which ships **no** identity component at all (this brick is an
**introduction**, not a migration). It removes nothing; the route/auth cutover
and Kong removal happen at B.8.10/B.8.14. Standard:
`.forge/standards/identity.yaml`.

> **Status**: the `full-stack-monorepo / 2.0.0` schema is a `candidate`
> (`scaffoldable: false`). This subtree is an additive on-disk asset spliced into
> the 2.0.0 stack at B.8.10/B.8.14; `forge init` still emits the flat 1.0.0 tree
> (no identity) by default. It is **not scaffoldable until B.8.14**.

## Delivery model — chart-referenced hybrid (ADR-B87-001)

Zitadel is **Atlas-installed from the upstream Helm chart**; this tree vendors
only the Forge **values overlay** + docs (no raw K8s manifests, no
`kustomization.yaml.tmpl`). The chart carries operator-grade machinery — an
`initJob` (DB schema/user/grants) and a `setupJob` (`zitadel setup`: first org +
human admin + machine user + K8s Secret generation) — that would require
significant re-implementation if vendoring raw manifests. The chart-referenced
hybrid mirrors the B.8.4 Envoy Gateway posture (ADR-B84-003).

| Plane | What | How |
|-------|------|-----|
| **Control + data plane** | Zitadel Deployment, login-UI Deployment, Service, initJob, setupJob, Secrets | Upstream Helm chart `zitadel/zitadel` (Atlas-provided install — below) |
| **Forge overlay** | masterkey ref, DSN secretKeyRef, FirstInstance config, Aegis annotations, securityContext, `postgresql.enabled: false` | `values-forge.yaml.tmpl` (this dir) |

