## Control-plane install (Atlas-provided)

```sh
helm repo add zitadel https://charts.zitadel.com
helm install zitadel zitadel/zitadel \
  --version 10.0.2 \
  -f values-forge.yaml \
  --set postgresql.enabled=false
```

- **`--set postgresql.enabled=false`** (or the equivalent `postgresql: {enabled:
  false}` already in `values-forge.yaml.tmpl`) suppresses the chart's bundled
  Bitnami postgresql subchart — we supply the **B.8.5 `fsm-db`** instead
  (ADR-B87-002). Do not let adopters pull a second Postgres.
- **Namespace**: deploy into the application namespace; the chart's `initJob` +
  `setupJob` Helm hooks run pre-install (weights 1 → 2) before the Deployment.

## Datastore (ADR-B87-002)

Zitadel **requires PostgreSQL 14+** (chart values.yaml line 26, verbatim:
*"ZITADEL requires PostgreSQL 14+ as its backing database"*). The B.8.5 datastore
ships `pgvector/pgvector:0.8.2-pg17` (Postgres **17** ≥ 14) — **compatible**.

- **Dev / shared posture**: a dedicated `zitadel` database + `zitadel_user` role
  on the shared B.8.5 `fsm-db` Postgres 17 instance. The DSN is injected via a K8s
  Secret (`secretKeyRef`); the chart `initJob` creates the schema/user/grants
  K8s-side. The dev compose fragment uses `depends_on: fsm-db`.
- **T2/T3 production posture**: a **dedicated Postgres instance** with network
  isolation (separate from the application datastore) is recommended.

## Login topology — dev vs K8s (ADR-B87-001, Q-004)

- **K8s** (`values-forge.yaml.tmpl`): `login.enabled: true` (chart default) — a
  **separate** `ghcr.io/zitadel/zitadel-login:v4.14.0` Deployment alongside the
  main Zitadel container. Realistic production topology.
- **Dev** (`docker-compose.fragment.yml.tmpl`): a **single** `fsm-zitadel` service
  using the main image with its **built-in** login interface (no separate login
  container — simpler dev stack). This is a deliberate dev/K8s difference, not an
  error.

## Secrets posture

> **NEVER PUT SECRETS HERE.**
> The masterkey and admin credentials are K8s Secrets generated at deploy time.
> No secret value is committed to the repository. See the bootstrap section below.

- **Masterkey**: "Must be exactly 32 bytes" (chart values.yaml P-06). Generate +
  pre-create the K8s Secret, then reference it by NAME via `masterkeySecretName`:
  ```sh
  kubectl create secret generic <project-name>-zitadel-masterkey \
    --from-literal=masterkey="$(tr -dc A-Za-z0-9 </dev/urandom | head -c 32)"
  ```
  (Placeholder command — the masterkey VALUE is never templated into the repo.)
- **DB DSN**: pre-create a K8s Secret with the connection string (which contains
  the password) and reference it via `valueFrom.secretKeyRef` (DSN mode, P-05):
  ```sh
  kubectl create secret generic <project-name>-zitadel-db \
    --from-literal=dsn="postgres://zitadel_user:<password>@<fsm-db-host>:5432/zitadel?sslmode=require"
  ```
  (Placeholder — `<password>` is supplied at deploy time, never committed.)

## Bootstrap (overview — full recipe in `bootstrap.md`)

1. **initJob** (Helm hook weight 1): creates the `zitadel` DB schema, user, grants.
2. **setupJob** (Helm hook weight 2): runs `zitadel setup` with the FirstInstance
   config → first org + human admin + machine user (IAM_OWNER); writes the machine
   user's PAT into a K8s Secret (named after the machine `Username`).
3. **Admin API recipe** (`bootstrap.md`): use the machine-user PAT to register the
   OIDC client application via the Management API. JWT signing-key rotation is
   Zitadel-managed (automatic). See `bootstrap.md` for the exact endpoints + cadence.

## Compliance posture — T1 / T2 / T3 (FR-B87-060)

Per `.forge/standards/global/compliance-tiers.md:121` (Zitadel row, verbatim):

| Tier | Posture | Verdict |
|------|---------|---------|
| **T1** | Zitadel Cloud SaaS (with a Data Processing Agreement) | ⚠️ Cloud SaaS T1 |
| **T2** | Zitadel self-hosted on EU infrastructure | ✅ self-host T2 |
| **T3** | Zitadel self-hosted on EU + SecNumCloud (OVHcloud / Scaleway / Outscale) | ✅ self-host EU+SecNumCloud |

> `compliance-tiers.md:121` — *"Zitadel | ⚠️ Cloud SaaS T1 | ✅ self-host T2 | ✅
> self-host EU+SecNumCloud | T3 = self-host obligatoire"*

This brick ratifies ADR-007 (`docs/ARCHITECTURE-TARGET.md`): Schrems II + the
CLOUD Act disqualify US-managed IdPs for EU-strict tiers, so Zitadel (Go, AGPL,
multi-tenant native) is the `default` in `identity.yaml`.

### J8-RULE-002 cross-reference (FR-B87-061)

The T3 refusal — `--eu-tier T3` + a non-self-host Zitadel → `[REFUSAL:]` exit 3 —
is **already enforced** by `bin/forge-init-fsm.sh` and the Janus orchestration
rules (`global/janus-orchestration-rules.md`, J8-RULE-002). This brick adds **no
new refusal logic**; it only makes the guarded `identity` component deployable.

