## Envoy → Zitadel OIDC delegation (FR-B87-063 — document-only)

Envoy Gateway (B.8.4 templates, `2.0.0/infra/k8s/envoy-gateway/`) delegates
authentication to Zitadel via OIDC — the target architecture relationship
`AT C4: Rel(envoy, zitadel, "OIDC")`. The intended shape: Envoy validates JWTs
issued by Zitadel at the gateway, and the Rust backend re-validates the bearer
token.

> The Envoy SecurityPolicy, JWTAuthn filter, and backend JWT validation
> middleware are NOT shipped in this brick. They are deferred to B.8.10 (Envoy
> OIDC wiring) and B.8.12 (E2E migration tests).

Shipping a minimal SecurityPolicy example here would require fabricating Envoy
Gateway API versions and Zitadel JWT issuer URL patterns that belong to B.8.10
design — Article III.4 bars this (ADR-B87-006; b8-coroot lesson).

## Scope out (this brick)

- **Envoy SecurityPolicy / JWT-filter wiring** → B.8.10 (Envoy OIDC wiring).
- **Backend Rust auth middleware** (bearer JWT validation) → B.8.12 (E2E tests).
- **Flutter / Qwik OIDC client** (PKCE, token storage) → B.8.10 / B.8.12.
- **Keycloak / Authentik alternative templates** — `identity.yaml` alternatives
  stay documentation-only; no alternative IdP templates ship here.
- **`identity.yaml` machine enforcement** (`linter_rule`, `ci_blocking`) — stays
  OFF; machine enforcement is a later brick (B.8.11 / B.8.14 territory).
